# Whiteboard engine protection

**Binding (2026-06-09, wb-chrome-redo hard-won lesson):**

`src/app/admin/students/[id]/whiteboard/[whiteboardSessionId]/workspace/WhiteboardWorkspaceClient.tsx`
is the core whiteboard engine. **Two successive chrome feature attempts (P1.1, P2) regressed
board separation and killed interactive controls** by rewriting this file.

## The rule

When touching `WhiteboardWorkspaceClient.tsx`:

**ALLOWED — additive extensions:**
- Adding new state variables, refs, and callbacks
- Adding new imports
- Adding new JSX render sections or replacing the render section layout
- Wiring NEW buttons/controls to EXISTING engine functions
- Adding new effects that call existing engine logic
- Adding new engine capability the new UI genuinely needs

**HARD STOP — behavioral changes:**
- Modifying or removing page/board switching logic (`selectTutorPage`, `addTutorPage`, `removeTutorPage`)
- Changing `pageDataRef` write or read semantics
- Rewriting the live-sync wiring (`handleExcalidrawChange`, `applyRemoteToCanvas`, broadcast/throttle effects)
- Modifying the recording lifecycle hook wiring (`evaluateLifecycle`, `derivePresentation`, FSM inputs)
- Refactoring or removing end-session flow logic

**If you find yourself needing to change existing engine behavior**, STOP and escalate to
the orchestrator. The constraint is behavioral — extend, don't rewrite.

## Known-good baseline

Commit `a150d4f` (PR-01 freedraw latency fix) is the board-separation-verified baseline.
Any chrome work should start from or verify against this commit.

